{"lemma":"خَزِّ","slug":"خَزِّ","root":"خ.ز.ز","root_slug":"خ-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10479","n10564"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of قَزّ (qazz, “silkware”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"],"examples":[{"text":"ومن الأهواز ونواحيها: السُّكَّر والدِّيباج الخَز.","english":"From al-Ahwaz one gets sugar and silk-brocades."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"marten"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"otter","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to poke, to sting, to pierce, to transfix"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Directly from Middle Persian [script needed] (kač). Doublet of قَزّ (qazz), which was borrowed via Aramaic.\n\nBorrowed from Persian خز (xaz).\n\nProbably from خ ص ص (ḵ ṣ ṣ) “to touch and thereby cut off”, senses seen more in خ ص ر (ḵ ṣ r), with Aramaic parallel in Classical Syriac ܐܶܬܚܰܙܰܙ (ʾetḥazzaz, “to penetrate”)."},"ipa":["/xazz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10479","headword_ar":"خَزٌّ","root":"xz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woven of wool and silk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of cloth entirely of silk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is the kind which one is forbidden to ride upon and to sit upon; not the former kind, which is allowable, and was sometimes worn by companions of the Prophet and by the next succeeding generation, as IAth has ascertained: (TA:) derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzazN","text_ar":"خُزَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) accord. to some: (TA:) or it is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thought by Golius to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beaver"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and afterwards applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloth made of its fur:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzuwzN","text_ar":"خُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, Msb, K.) [Golius seems to derive it from the Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qazo","text_ar":"قَزْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raw silk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and assigns to it also the meaning of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a coarser kind of spun silk."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzuwzN wabuzuwzN","text_ar":"خُزُوزٌ وَبُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good cloths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bz","text_ar":"بز"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n10564","headword_ar":"خَزٍ","root":"xzY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaziYa","text_ar":"خَزِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Base, abased, abject, rile, despicable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignominious."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xazoyaAnu","text_ar":"خَزْيَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxozFY","text_ar":"مُخْزًى"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}